This paper is about a spoken dialogue system, which involves natural language processing and human-computer interaction, making cs.CL and cs.HC the most likely categories. The system is also adaptable, which suggests the use of machine learning or artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI another likely category. The system retrieves train schedules on the web, which involves information retrieval, making cs.IR a possible category. Finally, the paper presents an empirical evaluation, which suggests the use of statistical methods or machine learning, making cs.LG a possible category.
